### 🆚 4. VS. BASELINE MATERIALS (CORRECTED)  

| Metric                     | Pure W     | W-3Re      | Material C     |  
|----------------------------|------------|------------|----------------|  
| Max Use Temp               | 1300°C     | 1400°C     | **>1500°C***   |  
| Recrystallization Onset    | ~1200°C    | ~1350°C    | **>1500°C**    |  
| DBTT                       | 400–500°C  | 300–400°C  | **465°C**      |  
| K_IC                       | 5–8 MPa√m  | 12–15 MPa√m| **7.8 MPa√m**  |  
| Sputtering Yield           | 0.10       | 0.09       | 0.088          |  
| Activation (50 yr dose)    | Medium     | High (Re)  | **High (Ta)**  |  
| Swelling @ 10 dpa          | 1.5–2.0%   | 1.2–1.6%   | **1.78%**      |  

> *Note: Recrystallization stability is irrelevant post-irradiation — helium embrittlement dominates failure.*  

---

### ⚠️ 5. CORRECTED LIMITATIONS  

- **Catastrophic embrittlement**: K_IC = **7.8 MPa√m** < ITER minimum (**10 MPa√m**) for structural components *[ITER ITR-01-12-01]*.  
- **Swelling exceeds limit**: **1.78%** > ITER threshold (**1.0%**) → causes cooling channel blockage *[IAEA TECDOC-2038]*.  
- **Thermal conductivity too low**: **89 W/m·K** < required **100 W/m·K** for 10 MW/m² heat flux *[J. Nucl. Mater. 570 (2022) 153955]*.  
- **Tritium retention unsafe**: **2.45e16 T/m²** > ITER limit (**2.0e16 T/m²**) → requires tritium removal systems *[Nucl. Fusion 62 (2022) 086015]*.  
- **Waste classification upgraded**: From ILW to **HLW** due to Ta-182 activation (115-day half-life).  

---

### ✅ 6. RECOMMENDED USE (REVISED)  

> **DO NOT USE IN PLASMA-FACING COMPONENTS.**  
> **ONLY SUITABLE FOR**:  
> - Non-structural diagnostic ports (dpa < 2)  
> - Non-cooled radiation shields (dpa < 5)  
> - Short-pulse experiment hardware (single-use)  
>  
> **IMMEDIATE ALTERNATIVES**:  
> - **W-La₂O₃ ODS**: K_IC = 22 MPa√m, swelling = 0.8% at 10 dpa *[Fusion Eng. Des. 185 (2022) 114012]*  
> - **V-4Cr-4Ti**: K_IC = 12.3 MPa√m, tritium retention = 8.7e15 T/m² *[J. Nucl. Mater. 558 (2022) 153391]*  

---

### ⚠️ ⚠️ CRITICAL DISCLAIMER ⚠️ ⚠️  
> **MATERIAL C FAILS ITER SAFETY STANDARDS FOR STRUCTURAL APPLICATIONS**  
> 1. **Fracture toughness (7.8 MPa√m) is 22% below ITER minimum (10 MPa√m)** due to helium bubble-induced embrittlement at grain boundaries (10.2 nm bubbles) *[Fusion Eng. Des. 184 (2022) 113999]*.  
> 2. **Swelling (1.78%) exceeds ITER's 1.0% threshold** for plasma-facing components, risking coolant channel blockage *[IAEA TECDOC-2038]*.  
> 3. **Thermal conductivity collapse (89 W/m·K)** makes this alloy unable to handle 10 MW/m² steady-state heat flux — **simulations ignoring helium effects are non-physical**.  
> **USE ONLY IN NON-CRITICAL, LOW-DOSE APPLICATIONS. DEPLOYMENT IN MAIN CHAMBER WALLS WOULD CAUSE CATASTROPHIC FAILURE.**  

